.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-NOTRACK 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.11.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-notrack \- connection tracking bypass rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I notrack
file defines flows that should bypass the kernel connection tracking
subsystem.  For each matching packet the compiler emits a
.B notrack
statement in the
.B prerouting raw
chain (nft priority
.BR -300 ).

Bypassing conntrack can significantly improve throughput for high-rate
flows (e.g. inter-router peering, monitoring traffic) at the cost of losing
stateful tracking for those flows.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/notrack
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
SOURCE	yes	Source zone:address or CIDR (or - for any)
DEST	yes	Destination zone:address or CIDR (or - for any)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Bypass tracking for high-rate BGP peering traffic:
.RS
.nf
#SOURCE          DEST             PROTO  DPORT
10.0.0.1         10.0.0.2         tcp    179
.fi
.RE
.PP
Bypass tracking for SNMP polling:
.RS
.nf
10.0.99.5        -                udp    161
.fi
.RE
.PP
Bypass tracking for all traffic on a monitoring interface:
.RS
.nf
mon              all
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-conntrack (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

